# msl Codebase Context

## Architecture
- **Host** (Swift + ObjC, macOS): `Sources/` ŌĆö CLI, daemon, VM manager, IPC, setup
- **Guest** (C, Linux/aarch64): `Guest/msld.c` ŌĆö daemon in Arch Linux ARM VM
- **Communication**: VSOCK (port 9999), Unix domain sockets (`~/.msl/msld.sock`, `~/.msl/msld.shell.sock`)
- **Build**: `make` compiles both host (Swift) and guest (C, cross-compiled with musl)
- **Distribution**: Homebrew tap at `github.com/xt9y/homebrew-msl` with 2 formulae (`msl.rb`, `msld.rb`)

## Files
| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `Sources/main.swift` | CLI entry point: `--start`, `--stop`, `--status`, `--exec`, `--shell`, `--setup`, `--version` |
| `Sources/Daemon.swift` | Host daemon: VM lifecycle, VSOCK relay, IPC handler, shell listener, socat health-check |
| `Sources/VM.swift` | `MSLVM` class: VM config (VZVirtualMachineConfiguration), boot/start/stop, VSOCK connect, execOnGuest |
| `Sources/IPC.swift` | `IPCServer` (daemon side, framed protocol), `IPCClient` (CLI side) |
| `Sources/State.swift` | `DaemonState`: PID file management |
| `Sources/Setup.swift` | `ensureSetup()`: downloads rootfs+kernel, configures rootfs, creates disk image, XQuartz/socat setup |
| `Sources/MSLVSOCK.h/.m` | ObjC bridge for VZVirtioSocketDevice (not exposed to Swift) |
| `Sources/BridgingHeader.h` | `#import "MSLVSOCK.h"` |
| `Guest/msld.c` | Guest daemon: VSOCK listener, shell (forkpty), exec (fork+pipe+waitpid) |
| `Resources/msl.entitlements` | Entitlements: virtualization, network server/client |
| `Makefile` | Build + codesign + release target |

## Key Data Paths
- VM data: `~/.msl/` (arch.img, kernel, daemon.pid, msld.sock, msld.shell.sock, machine-id)
- Serial log: `/tmp/msl-serial.log`
- X11 bridge: socat TCP:6000 ŌåÆ /tmp/.X11-unix/X0

## VSOCK Protocol
- Mode 0x00 = exec: `[0x00][4-byte BE cmd_len][command bytes]` ŌåÆ `[output...][4-byte BE exit_code]`
- Mode 0x01 = shell: bidirectional raw relay to PTY

## Known Issues (from security review)
1. HTTP downloads with no checksum ŌĆö must fix
2. Passwordless root ŌĆö document as conscious decision
3. Ad-hoc code signing ŌĆö needs Developer ID (out of scope for now)
4. Version drift ŌĆö Makefile doesn't verify tag matches MSLVersion
5. Hardcoded kernel version 6.8.0-136-generic ŌĆö breaks when Ubuntu prunes it
6. No retry/resume on downloads, no disk space check
7. Errors go to stdout only ŌĆö no log file
8. No CI, no tests
9. No upgrade path
10. CPU/memory hardcoded (2 vCPU / 2GB)
11. msld has no auth token
12. PID file race (no flock, stale PID possible)
13. No signal handling on daemon
14. No uninstall command
15. Raw mode not cleaned up on signal
16. chmod -R +r too broad